The victim was filmed three minutes later as he was pulled to his feet and robbed of his phone and wallet.

The video of Mr Rossli, who now has two metal plates in his jaw, became an internet sensation. David Cameron said it left him disgusted.

Isagba had denied grievous bodily harm and robbery. He will be sentenced on March 9 – the day after his 18th birthday.

Two other men charged with robbing Mr Rossli will stand trial at a later date.

